-- Centum Shares Fall Third Day to Two-Week Low in Nairobi
-- B y   E r i c   O m b o k
-- 2012-02-02T12:54:12Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-02-02/centum-falls-third-day-in-nairobi-heads-for-two-week-low-1-.html
Centum Investment Co., (CENTUM)   Kenya ’s
largest investment company, fell for a third day and closed at
its lowest in two weeks amid speculation investors are taking
profits.  The stock dropped 2.5 percent to 13.75 shillings by the
3:00 p.m. close in Nairobi, the lowest since Jan. 20, according
to data compiled by Bloomberg.  “It was really oversold in December, then it recovered in
January and now we are seeing very thin profit taking,” George Bodo, an equity strategist at Nairobi-based Apex Africa Capital
said by phone today.  The stock hit a 12-month trough of 11.30 shillings on Dec.
9 and has rallied 22 percent since then, according to data
compiled by Bloomberg.  To contact the reporter on this story:
